A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Code Section 40-13-2.1 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to
2 signature on citations required, effect of failure to sign, exemption for out-of-state drivers,
3 and electronic capture of signature, so as to provide for the issuance of a refusal to sign
4 citation; to provide for a penalty; to provide for related matters; to repeal conflicting laws;
5 and for other purposes.
6 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
7 SECTION 1.
8 Code Section 40-13-2.1 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to signature on
9 citations required, effect of failure to sign, exemption for out-of-state drivers, and electronic
10 capture of signature, is amended by revising subsection (a) as follows:
11 "(a) A person who is issued a citation as provided in this chapter or Code Section 17-6-11,
12 relating to display of driver's license in lieu of bail, shall may sign the citation to
13 acknowledge receipt of the citation and of his or her obligation to appear for trial. The
14 officer shall advise the person that signing the citation is not an admission of guilt and that
15 failure to sign will result in the person having to post a cash bond appear for trial. If the
16 person refuses to sign the citation, it shall constitute reasonable cause to believe that the
